  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Economic empowerment of 50 women in Soma,Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After a devastating mining disaster in coal mining town of Soma, Manisa, Turkey 301 miners were killed and nearly 3000 miners became unemployed. Their female relatives suddenly found themselves as the sole breadwinners in their families. Anatolian Artisans has organized the women to start a cooperative where they can make products using their traditional skills. They need funding to include more women expanding their workshop.</narrative>
  </description>
